216.3	Scoville_scale	Scoville scale	The Scoville scale is a measurement of the spicy heat (or piquance) of a chili pepper. The number of Scoville heat units (SHU) indicates the amount of capsaicin present. Capsaicin is a chemical compound that stimulates chemoreceptor nerve endings in the skin, especially the mucous membranes; capsaicin itself has a Scoville rating of 16,000,000 SHU.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/PepperswithscovilleCentralMarketHoustonTX.JPG/330px-PepperswithscovilleCentralMarketHoustonTX.JPG
